location.name: Point Pelee National Park (general location for observations within the park)

mediaNotes: Small flock of 5 birds chattering to one another near shore - unfortunately, wave action overpowers sound of birds a bit.
Vocalizations are near the start of the recording.
poor recording with too much rain noise; calls at 53 sec and about 1:15 perhaps earlier as well.

There are BRBL in the foreground, but their calls were the high pitch soft chattery calls. The gave a much lower pitch grunt call, but did not capture it. The flock consisted of about 20 GRSC, a mixture of males and females, near the shoreline so confident these calls weren’t made by the huge LESC flock found at least 200+ yards away upriver.
